title: Axes don't match error while trying to enumerate data loader
body_html:
Hi, I was trying to run the vnet implementation in pytorch
(https://github.com/mattmacy/vnet.pytorch) and after normalising the scans with 512, 512, 500, 0.7 for x_max, y_max, z_max, voxspacing, when I call the train function on the line where the for loop is enumerating through the data loader I get a axes don't match array error. I am not understand how to fix this. Any help would be really helpful. I am a newbie in machine learning

Thanks
Abhishek
